The Parcel Number follows this structure:


I-Z-S-PPP-ppp-CCCC


Where:

I → Island Number (removed in the search).

Z → Zone Number.

S → Section Number.

PPP → Plat Number (three digits).

ppp → Parcel Number (three digits).

CCCC → CPR or Condominium Number (if none, four zeros are added).


Steps to adjust it:


Example with APN from Cyborg: 312031007

  • Remove the Island Number (I) → If the first number represents the Island Number, you must remove it.
  • Ensure the Plat Number (PPP) and Parcel Number (ppp) have three digits each → If they have fewer, add leading zeros.
  • If there is no CPR or Condominium Number (CCCC), add four zeros at the end.


Analyzing the number 312031007:


3 → Island Number (removed).

12 → Zone-Section.

031 → Plat Number (already has three digits, correct).

007 → Parcel Number (already has three digits, correct).

No CPR/Condominium Number, so four zeros are added at the end.


The corrected number would be:

120310070000
